1. Primary Auxiliary Verbs (Helping verbs for tenses, voices, questions, negatives):
Be (am, is, are, was, were, being, been)
Example: She is running.
(ती धावत आहे.)

Have (have, has, had, having)
Example: They have finished the work.
(त्यांनी काम पूर्ण केले आहे.)

Do (do, does, did)
Example: Do you like tea?
(तुला चहा आवडतो का?)

2. Modal Auxiliary Verbs (Express ability, possibility, permission, obligation, etc.):
Can
Example: She can swim.
(ती पोहू शकते.)

Could
Example: I could help you yesterday.
(मी काल तुला मदत करू शकलो होतो.)

May
Example: You may leave now.
(तू आता जाऊ शकतोस.)

Might
Example: It might rain today.
(आज पाऊस पडू शकतो.)

Shall
Example: Shall we start?
(आपण सुरुवात करू का?)

Should
Example: You should see a doctor.
(तुला डॉक्टरांकडे जावे लागेल.)

Will
Example: I will call you tomorrow.
(मी उद्या तुला फोन करीन.)

Would
Example: Would you like some coffee?
(तुला कॉफी पाहिजे का?)

Must
Example: You must wear a seatbelt.
(तुला सीटबेल्ट बांधणे आवश्यक आहे.)

Ought to
Example: You ought to apologize.
(तुला माफी मागावी लागेल.)




| Positive                 | Comparative                         | Superlative                              |
| ------------------------ | ----------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| She is **tall**.         | She is **taller** than me.          | She is the **tallest** in class.         |
| The weather is **cold**. | Today is **colder** than yesterday. | This is the **coldest** day of the year. |
| He is **fast**.          | He runs **faster** than his friend. | He is the **fastest** runner here.       |

1. Positive Degree (साधा दर्जा)
This book is good.
हे पुस्तक चांगले आहे.

2. Comparative Degree (तुलनात्मक दर्जा)
This book is better than that one.
हे पुस्तक त्या पुस्तकापेक्षा चांगले आहे.

3. Superlative Degree (उत्तम दर्जा)
This is the best book in the library.
हे ग्रंथालयातील सर्वोत्तम पुस्तक आहे


